response: "{ \"title\": \"Coin Change\", \"description\": \"You have a set of coins with denominations 1, 5 and 10. You are given a total amount, write a function to find the number of ways you can make up this amount using these coins.\\n\\n#### Function Signature\\n```python\\ndef count_ways(amount: int) -> int:\\n```\\n\\n#### Input\\n- `amount` (int): The total amount to be made up using the coins.\\n\\n#### Output\\n- Returns the number of ways you can make up the given amount using the available coins.\", \"code\": \"\\nimport math\\n\\ndef count_ways(amount: int) -> int:\\n    ways = [0] * (amount + 1)\\n    ways[0] = 1\\n    for coin in [1, 5, 10]:\\n        for i in range(coin, amount + 1):\\n            ways[i] += ways[i - coin]\\n    return ways[amount]\\n\\n\", \"tests\": [\"assert count_ways(15) == 4\", \"assert count_ways(20) == 9\", \"assert count_ways(5) == 2\", \"assert count_ways(3) == 1\"] }"
